Chilean Stock Movers: Cencosud, Hites, Ripley and Vapores Fall

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-06-14T21:27:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-14/chilean-stock-movers-cap-sa-advances-cencosud-and-ripley-fall.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:11 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index fell 0.4 percent to 4,646.13.  Cencosud SA (CENCOSUD CC) fell 1.5 percent to 3,366.4
pesos, and was the most active by value today with 8.2 billion
pesos ($17.6 million) changing hands.  Latin America ’s third-
largest retailer retreated on speculation that irregularities at
rival  Empresas La Polar SA (LAPOLAR)  could lead to tighter regulations for
retailers with credit card operations, German Guerrero, a
director at brokerage firm MBI Inversiones, said.  Ripley Corp SA (RIPLEY)   followed suit, retreating 0.6
percent to 576.89 pesos, its fourth day of losses while  Empresas
Hites SA (HITES)   fell 4.8 percent to 597.09 pesos, its lowest
price in seven months.  Cia. Sudamericana de Vapores SA (VAPORES CC) retreated 3.7
percent to 280.16 pesos, the steepest fall in almost three
weeks. Latin America’s largest container shipping company was
reiterated at “sell” and had its price estimate cut by
Santiago-based brokerage firm Larrain Vial SA to 280 pesos from
330 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
